lestone":null,"comments":1,"created_at":"2022-11-15T20:33:51Z","updated_at":"2022-11-16T16:09:11Z","closed_at":null,"author_association":"MEMBER","active_lock_reason":null,"draft":false,"pull_request":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/pulls/47585","html_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/47585","diff_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/47585.diff","patch_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/47585.patch","merged_at":null},"body":"The annotations should be safe. For me, this speeds up the computation by a factor of 2. It's not entirely clear why switching to `for i in diagind(A) t += A[i] end` doesn't improve the performance, but makes it a tiny bit worse.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/47585/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/47585/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null},"comment":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/comments/1317266134","html_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/47585#issuecomment-1317266134","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/47585","id":1317266134,"node_id":"IC_kwDOABkWpM5Og-LW","user":{"login":"thchr","id":26799210,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI2Nzk5MjEw","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/26799210?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/thchr","html_url":"https://github.com/thchr","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/thchr/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/thchr/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/thchr/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/thchr/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/thchr/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/thchr/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/thchr/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/thchr/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/thchr/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2022-11-16T16:09:11Z","updated_at":"2022-11-16T16:09:11Z","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"> It's not entirely clear why switching to `for i in diagind(A) t += A[i] end` doesn't improve the performance, but makes it a tiny bit worse.

Essentially a reformulation of this comment, but wanted to add: this is related to iteration over `j in diagind(A)` (updating `j` by adding `n+1` at every iteration) being slower than evaluating the diagonal index at every iteration (by `j = i + (i-1)*n`), but only for small matrix sizes:
```jl
function iterate_diagind(A)
    s = 0
    @simd for j in diagind(A) # aka `1:n+1:n^2`
        s += j * 1.0 # <--- avoids the loop being optimized away
    end
    s
end
function iterate_muladd(A)
    n = size(A, 1)
    s = 0
    @simd for i in 1:n
        j = i + (i-1)*n # aka `muladd(i-1, n, i)`
        s += j * 1.0 # <--- avoids the loop being optimized away
    end
    s
end

A = rand(10, 10)
@btime iterate_diagind($A);
  13.126 ns (0 allocations: 0 bytes)   # A = rand(10,10)
  32.359 ns (0 allocations: 0 bytes)   # A = rand(50,50)
  836.486 ns (0 allocations: 0 bytes)  # A = rand(1000,1000)
@btime iterate_muladd($A);
  6.800 ns (0 allocations: 0 bytes)    # A = rand(10,10)
  23.996 ns (0 allocations: 0 bytes)   # A = rand(50,50)
  823.171 ns (0 allocations: 0 bytes)  # A = rand(1000,1000)
```
