The generalization of this for concatenation along multiple dimensions, e.g. `cat(A, B, dims=(1,2))` to `cat(A, B, dims=Val((1,2))`, doesn't work currently due to a missing specialization of `Base.dims2cat` for `Val(<:NTuple)`. This PR adds that and makes `cat(A, B, dims=Val(1,2,...))` work.

On this PR:
```jl
julia> @code_warntype cat(rand(2,2), rand(2,2), dims=Val((1,2)))
MethodInstance for (::Base.var"#cat##kw")(::NamedTuple{(:dims,), Tuple{Val{(1, 2)}}}, ::typeof(cat), ::Matrix{Float64}, ::Matrix{Float64})
  from (::Base.var"#cat##kw")(::Any, ::typeof(cat), A...) in Base at abstractarray.jl:1861
Arguments
  _::Core.Const(Base.var"#cat##kw"())
  @_2::Core.Const((dims = Val{(1, 2)}(),))
  @_3::Core.Const(cat)
  A::Tuple{Matrix{Float64}, Matrix{Float64}}
Locals
  dims::Val{(1, 2)}
  @_6::Val{(1, 2)}
Body::Matrix{Float64}
[... omitted]
```
